ic-paragraph">In a similar vein, the Greeks called a pair of integers <span=
 id=3D"ref796460"></span><a href=3D"https://www.britannica.com/science/amic=
able-numbers" class=3D"md-crosslink " data-show-preview=3D"true">amicable</=
a> (=E2=80=9Cfriendly=E2=80=9D) if each was the sum of the proper divisors =
